Some Kerio Valley youth have urged Kanu chairman Gideon Moi (pictured) to stop politicising the war on cattle rustling. Kerio Youths Association chairman Joel Kimaiyo said it is wrong for Gideon to criticise Deputy President William Ruto&rsquo;s peace meetings in the troubled Baringo and Elgeyo Marakwet.Gideon said on Saturday Ruto&rsquo;s visits are inconsequential.